# GrieveGently — Cursor Rules
# grievegently.com

## Project
This is the landing page for GrieveGently at grievegently.com.
Next.js 16 (App Router) · TypeScript · Tailwind CSS v4 · Framer Motion.

## Tailwind v4
Global styles use `@import "tailwindcss"` in src/app/globals.css — not the v3 `@tailwind base/components/utilities` directives.
Extend the design system with `@theme { }` in that file; keep shared semantic colours in `:root` for `var(--*)` in components.
tailwind.config.ts is content paths only.

## The most important rule
ALL copy lives in src/lib/content.ts. Never hardcode text strings in components.
When adding new sections, add the data to content.ts first, then import it.

## Design tokens
Never hardcode hex values. Always use CSS custom properties (light theme — see src/app/globals.css :root):

  var(--bg)       warm off-white page background
  var(--bg-2)     alternate sections
  var(--bg-3)     subtle panels / inputs
  var(--card)     card / dropdown surfaces
  var(--card-active)  selected pillar tab background
  var(--text)     primary text
  var(--muted)    secondary text
  var(--dim)      tertiary / legal footer
  var(--accent)   gold — Estate pillar (tuned for contrast on light)
  var(--blue)     Admin pillar
  var(--green)    Wellbeing pillar
  var(--border)   default borders
  var(--shadow-card)  var(--shadow-float)  var(--shadow-dropdown)  elevation
  var(--surface-hover)  nav / menu hover wash

## Typography
  Default → body + Tailwind `font-sans` → Nunito (`@theme --font-sans`). Use `font-brand` for explicit brand UI (alias of legacy `font-nunito`).
  Headlines → `font-serif` + `font-extrabold` → Nunito 800; `em`/`i` → Fraunces semibold italic.
  Long / dense reading → `font-reading` → DM Sans (hero lede, section paragraphs, cards’ body copy, FAQ answers, testimonials, compare-scroll step bodies, footer, nav dropdown descriptions, etc.).
  Never use Inter, Arial, Roboto as headline fonts.

## Component rules
  - Client components need "use client" at the top
  - Use useAudience() from @/lib/audienceContext for audience-aware content
  - Use cn() from @/lib/utils for conditional classes
  - Use useScrollReveal() hook + fade-up class for scroll animations
  - One section per file, keep components focused

## Pillar colours (nav + accents)
  estate    → var(--accent)   — `#pillar-estate` on probate row in Solution
  admin     → var(--blue)    — `#pillar-admin` on funeral-planning row
  wellbeing → var(--green)   — `#pillar-wellbeing` on “Getting grief support” accordion row

## File paths
  @/components/nav/        Nav.tsx, ToggleBar.tsx
  @/components/hero/       Hero.tsx
  @/components/solution/   Solution.tsx
  @/components/sections/   Problem, Impact, B2BSection, Pain, Science,
                           Testimonials, Who, Faq, Cta
  @/components/ui/         Footer, Logo.tsx, shared primitives
  public/images/           Brand assets (e.g. grievegently-logo.svg)
  @/lib/content.ts         All copy and data (`solutionCareSection`, `impactSection`, …)
  @/lib/audienceContext.tsx Audience state
  @/lib/useScrollReveal.ts Scroll animation hook
  @/types/index.ts         TypeScript interfaces

## Domain
  Production: grievegently.com
  Platform:   Vercel (see README for deployment steps)
  Region:     lhr1 (London)

## Image placeholders
  Phone mockups in Hero.tsx and Solution.tsx are currently coded UI.
  When real screenshots are ready: use next/image, drop files in public/images/.
  Mark all placeholders with // TODO: swap with real screenshot

## When adding new sections
  1. Add data/copy to src/lib/content.ts
  2. Add types to src/types/index.ts if needed
  3. Create component in appropriate folder
  4. Import in src/app/page.tsx
  5. Never hardcode copy in the component itself
